<HEADLINE>
2 killed, 40 injured in bus accident in Nepal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, Dec. 2 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
At least two persons were killed and 40 others were injured when
a passenger bus bound for Kilchowk from Gorkha fell down 100
meter below the road in Tanahun district in western Nepal on
Saturday night, THT Online reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to police, the two persons died while being rushed to a
hospital.
</P>
<P>
As many as  21 persons are critically injured and undergoing
treatment in Gadaki zonal hospital, Pokhara, some 200 km west of
Kathmandu, while 19 others are undergoing treatment at Damuali
hospital.
</P>
<P>
The passengers were returning home after having a picnic in
Gorkha, the report said.
</P>
